# Melu Design System

**Source of truth:** `docs/frontend-design-system.md`

## Rules

1. **Use design tokens** — Never hardcode hex colors or magic spacing. Use `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-border`, `px-page`, `p-card`, `gap-section-gap`.

2. **Use primitives** — Import from `src/app/components/design-system/`. Use `ScreenShell`, `TopBar`, `MeluCard`, `Button` (variants `melu` / `meluOutline`), `ChatBubble`, `ResponseChip`, `MealCard`, `WeekSummaryCard`, `ProfileRowCard` before building custom UI.

3. **Prohibited patterns** — No swap button (V1 is approve-only). No calendar sync references. Bottom nav only on HomeDashboard, ComingUp, WeeklyPlanView.

4. **Before creating new UI** — Check if a primitive exists. If a pattern repeats, extract to a primitive.
